gary has been working in the alternative market for twenty years having held positions in bermuda hawaii vermont and south carolina  he has been involved in the establishment of numerous single parent captives association captives risk retention groups and traditional group insurance programs  he is a frequent industry speaker and has spoken at the cpcu annual meeting rims the american society of association executives’ conference the casualty actuarial society conference ibc conference self insurance institute of america conference as well as captive industry conferences in hawaii vermont south carolina arizona tennessee and cayman  in addition he is a regular contributor to industry publications and has been published and quoted in captive review captive times business insurance risk and insurance national underwriter and the risk retention reporter  captive review recently ranked gary as number  in the “power ” for the alternative risk industry gary has served as treasurer of the hawaii captive insurance council as chairman of the legislative committee and member of the finance and conference committees for the vermont captive insurance association as a director of the national risk retention association where he currently participates on the legislative committee as a faculty member for the international center for captive insurance education and as a founding member of the tennessee captive insurance association gary joined usa risk group in october  as head of the company’s hawaii operations and relocated back to vermont in november  where he was promoted to senior vice president of usa risk group  gary was promoted to president of usa risk group in july   from february  to october  gary was vice president of sedgwick management services us limited in hawaii  during this time gary was responsible for the hawaiian domiciled captives of sedgwick management services us limited in october  gary joined price waterhouse in bermuda and worked on the audits of a number of captive insurance companies  he moved to marsh  mclennan bermuda in june  as an account manager and relocated to vermont in december  where he accepted a position with johnson  higgins services as an account manager  he was promoted to assistant vice president and senior account manager in march   as an account manager he was responsible for providing accounting and reporting services for a variety of captive and other nontraditional insurance companies a native of glasgow scotland gary attended the university of glasgow receiving his bachelor of accounting in   he qualified as a member of the scottish institute of chartered accountants in  and received the association of risk management designation in  our team spencer capital holdings to acquire usa risk group  business wire spencer capital holdings to acquire usa risk group usa risk will add to spencer capital’s insurance offering diversifying its product base february    am eastern standard time new yorkbusiness wirespencer capital holdings ltd “spencer capital” a valueoriented global investment firm has agreed to acquire usa risk group “usa risk” the largest independent captive insurance manager in the world the transaction is subject to customary closing requirements and regulatory approval and is expected to close during the first quarter of  usa risk currently serves over  clients holding  billion assets under management financial terms of the transaction were not disclosed usa risk is an independent captive insurance manager founded in  by h lincoln miller jr a leader in helping to enact legislation enabling vermont to become the preeminent captive domicile within the united states usa risk has since established member companies in  additional strategic locations servicing  captive domiciles inside and outside the us market usa risk currently has  employees on and offshore the acquisition of usa risk is immediately accretive to spencer capital and is complementary to its existing portfolio of companies the financial and operational support of spencer capital will provide usa risk with the opportunity to grow and expand its client capabilities while maintaining its longstanding autonomy spencer re a reinsurance subsidiary of spencer capital holdings and usa risk are expected to be mutual beneficiaries from crossselling opportunities “usa risk’s unparalleled reputation and leadership position in the captive industry is a welcomed addition to spencer capital holdings as we seek to assemble a robust platform of leading and valuedriven companies in the insurance and financial services industries” said ken shubin stein chairman of spencer capital commenting on the transaction h lincoln miller jr group chairman of usa risk said “we have been approached by many suitors over the years but until we met the team at spencer capital we did not view a transaction as being in the best interests of our customers and employees ken shubin stein and his team embody the same ethos we instil in our employees and we share the same longterm interests for growing usa risk this also allows us to maintain our longheld philosophy of independence from conflicts of brokerowned managers” after the transaction closing usa risk will keep its name and continue to operate as it has effectively done for over  years miller currently group chairman of usa risk will join the board of directors of spencer capital and gary osborne currently president of usa risk will join the board of directors of spencer re spencer capital holdings ltd spencer capital holdings a global holding company owns spencer re a reinsurance firm focused on the american auto dealership industry and is affiliated with spencer capital management a valueoriented investment management firm spencer capital management provides support to philanthropic endeavours including crutches  kids a nonprofit organization devoted to helping children with physical disabilities walk spencer capital holdings was founded in  by chairman dr ken shubi