unded by dr ken shubin stein in  spencer capital management is a global investment advisor based in new york city drawing upon dr shubin stein’s dual backgrounds in the fields of medicine and financial services the firm takes a concentrated value oriented and systematic approach to investing in the global equity markets the firm’s sharp focus on processes is one of its defining aspects and has allowed it to develop a specialized investing approach that recognizes and reduces biases that can distort decision making drive unconscious behaviors and ultimately suboptimal investing decisions leadership kenneth shubin stein md cfa – founder  portfolio manager dr ken shubin stein is the founder and portfolio manager of spencer capital management llc and the chairman of spencer capital holdings ltd he is a graduate of the albert einstein college of medicine where he completed a year medical and research program with a focus on molecular genetics he graduated with a ba degree from columbia college with dual concentrations in premedical studies and political science ken holds the cfa designation and is an adjunct professor at the columbia university graduate school of business ken is also chairman emeritus of the manhattan chapter of ypo and founder and chairman of crutches  kids a notforprofit organization dedicated to providing crutches to children in need around the world giving back aligned with spencer capital management’s scientific investing model is the firm’s commitment to philanthropy the firm takes the same methodological and process driven investing approach to helping others dr shubin stein’s foundation crutcheskids collects and distributes crutches to children in need globally the organization’s ability to effectuate change by providing a real solution to a tangible problem is what makes it such a unique platform visit crutches  kids overview leadership giving back about us investing style contact us × vernon leake  spencer capital skip to content our team verno